This paper deals with the alignment and registration of 3D facial scans, which involves computer vision (CV) techniques such as point cloud processing and mesh warping. Therefore, cs.CV is the most likely sub-category. The paper also involves geometric modeling (GR) and computational geometry (CG) techniques for representing and manipulating the 3D models. Additionally, the paper mentions the use of iterative methods, which are commonly used in robotics (RO) for solving optimization problems. Finally, the paper deals with the accuracy of the scans, which could fall under the sub-category of multimedia (MM) for measuring and evaluating the quality of digital media.
